tion. He writes with unmatched intensity and a unique sensitivity to the human tragicomedy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCollege teachersvFiction. 0aCollege teachersxFiction. 0aExilesvFiction. 0aExilesxFiction. 0aThreatsvFiction. 0aThreatsxFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aMarian, Oana Sanziana, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300183467423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300183467.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles